#Text=UEFA Euro 2016 , day 12 : Ukraine-Poland , Northern Ireland-Germany , Czech Republic-Turkey and Croatia-Spain
#Text=Friday , June 24 , 2016
#Text=On Tuesday , in UEFA Euro 2016 , Poland defeated Ukraine 1 – 0 , Germany defeated Northern Ireland 1 – 0 , Czech Republic lost 0 – 2 to Turkey and Croatia defeated Spain 2 – 1 .
#Text=Poland , Germany , Spain , and Croatia have all qualified for the Last 16 knockout phase .
#Text=File photo of Mario GomezImage : Steindy .
#Text=Group C — Ukraine 0 – 1 Poland
#Text=After Poland drew 0 – 0 against Germany , Robert Lewandowski led them against Ukraine in their final group match .
#Text=Two Ukrainian players were booked in the first half .
#Text=Jakub Błaszczykowski
#Text=scored the only goal of the game for the Poles in the 54th minute .
#Text=Poland won 1 – 0 and advanced to the Last 16 knockout phase of the tournament by finishing second in the Group C table with 7 points .
#Text=Ukraine finished last in the table and have been eliminated .
#Text=Group C — Northern Ireland 0 – 1 Germany
#Text=Bayern Munich
#Text=goalkeeper Manuel Neuer led Germany against Northern Ireland .
#Text=Mario Gomez
#Text=scored the only goal of the match just before the half-hour mark as Germany won the game 1 – 0 .
#Text=Germany have qualified for the Last 16 round , finishing first in Group C table with 7 points — edging above Poland on goal difference .
#Text=Group D — Czech Republic 0 – 2
#Text=Turkey
#Text=Turkey struck early as Burak Yılmaz found the net in the 10th minute .
#Text=Ozan Tufan

#Text=' s goal in the second half was enough for the Turks to claim three points and finish third in Group D. The Czech Republic were eliminated from the tournament , finishing last in the group table with one point .
#Text=Group D — Croatia 2 – 1 Spain
#Text=Ivan Rakitić
#Text=faced his FC Barcelona teammate Andrés Iniesta as Croatia played Spain . Álvaro Morata scored an early goal for Spain in the 7th minute , providing the defending champions an early lead .
#Text=But Nikola Kalinić scored a tap-in in the 45th minute to equalise for the Croats .
#Text=In the second half , Spain won a penalty , but Spanish captain Sergio Ramos ' s kick was saved by Danijel Subašić .
#Text=In the 87th minute , Ivan Perišić scored the winning goal for Croatia , and they qualified for the Last 16 stage by finishing first in the Group D table .
#Text=Croatia were undefeated in the group stage .
#Text=Spain , second in Group D , also qualified for the knockout phase .
#Text=Ukraine
